# Project Title

Physics-Informed Deep Learning for Wave Propagation

## Overview

The objective is to investigate how neural networks can approximate wave propagation by incorporating the governing physical laws directly into the training process, eliminating the need for labeled simulation data. The project demonstrates PINN formulation, training, and comparison with analytical solutions for wave propagation problems.

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/akashitasar/WavePINN.git
cd WavePINN

## Requirements

- Python 3.11
- NumPy
- TensorFlow

## Running the Code

```bash
python main.py
```

## Citation

If you use this code, please cite:

Akashita Sareen. *Wave Equation PINN*. GitHub repository, 2026.

## Attribution

This repository is derived from the work of the authors of:

https://github.com/okada39/pinn_wave.git

Their implementation served as the starting point for this project. Subsequent modifications adapted the code to solve an impact-driven wave propagation problem, with ongoing efforts to tune the network hyperparameters for improved solution convergence. Additional changes included refining the temporal discretization, improving result visualization and plotting, and evaluating the accuracy and stability of the predicted wave response.

